        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34201",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rockaut",
                        "name": "rockaut",
                        "displayName": "Markus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I like it :D\n\nOnly thing i dont get: Cache and Session are available Resource Plugins, why not  only use  this?\n\nBut the Disable feature is nice, would like to see this for Res-Plug-Ins too.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rockaut",
                        "name": "rockaut",
                        "displayName": "Markus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-02T23:51:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-02T23:51:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34207",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chielsen",
                        "name": "chielsen",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Thalen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well cache isn't available AFAIK and the session resource doesn't do what this does.\nBUT, this is only an example about how it would work.\nResourceplugins you can disable already by just removing them from the resource config.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chielsen",
                        "name": "chielsen",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Thalen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-03T03:43:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-03T03:43:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36527",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chielsen",
                        "name": "chielsen",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Thalen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "updated it",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chielsen",
                        "name": "chielsen",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Thalen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-26T13:57:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-26T13:57:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36532",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would personally like to see some benchmarks about this. Though the feature is nice, it's not essential imho, and it has the potential of slowing down every app based on zend_app.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-27T05:18:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-27T05:18:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36535",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chielsen",
                        "name": "chielsen",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Thalen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I did 2 runs of 10k, results are the patch hardly makes a difference (only a bit faster).\r\nSee the attached results and files i ran the test with.\r\n\r\nNotice that there is no checking if the options actually exists (so results in a notice error) in the 'old' implementation. An extra check would only make it slower.\r\n\r\nAlso, since you are saving the config into a local variable, more calls to the getOptions or a bigger config file will make it slower.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chielsen",
                        "name": "chielsen",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Thalen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-27T06:45:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-27T06:45:41.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
